Procedure*Text: In this section, you will be presented with a series of word pairs.
As you study, you will be asked to count the total number of vowels (a, e, i, o, u) within the two words. Please note that y is not considered a vowel.

For example, if you are given the pair CAT - DOG, CAT has one vowel and DOG has one vowel. The correct response would be 2 (1 + 1 = 2). After typing the number, you will press ENTER to move to the next pair.
You will now begin the study. Press Enter when you are ready to begin.
